8:
He will fly away like a dream and will not be found;
\q indeed, he will be chased away like a vision of the night.
\q

10:
His children will apologize to poor people;
\q his hands will have to give back his wealth.
\q

15:
He swallows down riches, but he will vomit them up again;
\q God will cast them out of his stomach.
\q

18:
He will give back the fruit of his labor and will not be able to eat it;
\q he will not enjoy the wealth earned by his commerce.
\q

21:
There is nothing left that he did not devour;
\q therefore his prosperity will not be permanent.
\q

23:
When he is about to fill his stomach, God will throw the fierceness of his wrath on him;
\q God will rain it down on him while he is eating.
\q

25:
The arrow will pierce through his back and will emerge;
\q indeed, the glittering point will come out through his liver;
\q terrors come on him.

26:
Complete darkness is reserved for his treasures;
\q a fire not fanned will devour him;
\q it will consume what is left in his tent.
\q

28:
The wealth of his house will vanish;
\q his goods will flow away on the day of God's wrath.
\q
